   Here is the the 64-36 roll call by which the
Senate sustained President Bush's veto of an Amtrak authorization
bill.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to override the veto and
pass the bill and a ``no'' vote was a vote to sustain the veto. It
would have taken 67 votes to override.
   Voting ``yes'' were 54 Democrats and 10 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 1 Democrat and 35 Republicans.
